1
00:00:04,805 --> 00:00:07,622
<i>They train doctors. Slowly.</i>

2
00:00:07,724 --> 00:00:09,924
<i>They watch us practice on frogs</i>

3
00:00:10,026 --> 00:00:12,360
<i>and pigs and dead people,</i>

4
00:00:12,463 --> 00:00:16,181
<i>and then live people.
They drill us relentlessly.</i>

5
00:00:16,283 --> 00:00:18,166
<i>They raise us like children.</i>

6
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,602
<i>And eventually, they
take a cold, hard boot</i>

7
00:00:20,704 --> 00:00:23,204
<i>and they kick us
out of the nest.</i>

8
00:00:23,306 --> 00:00:25,807
I have great faith
in you. Great faith.

9
00:00:25,926 --> 00:00:29,611
I can because I chose
you. I trained you.

10
00:00:29,713 --> 00:00:32,097
I've watched you work.
I know what you can do.

11
00:00:32,199 --> 00:00:36,417
That's why today's different. The
training wheels are coming off, people.

12
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:38,653
I'm throwing down the
gauntlet today, people.

13
00:00:38,755 --> 00:00:42,507
I've got a million dollar surplus,
and one department gets it.

14
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:45,460
You know what you need
and I know what you need.

15
00:00:45,562 --> 00:00:49,847
Now, I want to know what you want.
And I'm gonna keep the residents busy.

16
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:54,736
Very busy. So that'll give you
time to put your best foot forward.

17
00:00:54,838 --> 00:00:56,938
- Navy scrubs?
- Attending scrubs.

18
00:00:57,040 --> 00:01:00,759
You are attendings today.
Run the cases. Take point.

19
00:01:00,861 --> 00:01:04,129
But don't be a fool. If you get
in over your head, cry "uncle."

20
00:01:04,231 --> 00:01:07,215
Until then, congratulations.

21
00:01:07,318 --> 00:01:09,301
You've just been promoted.

22
00:01:11,655 --> 00:01:16,124
Um, Chief Webber? Sorry.
I-I didn't get any scrubs.

23
00:01:16,226 --> 00:01:18,346
This is for fourth-year
residents only, Grey.

24
00:01:18,378 --> 00:01:20,218
It's just a regular day for you.

25
00:01:20,247 --> 00:01:24,882
Fine. If they're gonna be attendings,
that makes me chief resident.

26
00:01:24,985 --> 00:01:29,488
- That makes you
our scut monkey.
- No, it doesn't.

27
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:31,723
Does... Does it? It doesn't!

28
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:48,873
The attendings aren't going anywhere.
We're basically just playing dress-up.

29
00:01:48,975 --> 00:01:50,642
Yeah.

30
00:01:58,419 --> 00:02:00,212
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

31
00:02:00,236 --> 00:02:04,039
- Are you sure this
is a good idea?
- Of course it is.

32
00:02:04,140 --> 00:02:06,775
We all did it. It's the
evolution of the craft.

33
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:10,945
The passing of the torch. The
lifeblood of the training process.

34
00:02:13,283 --> 00:02:16,384
Here you go. Here you go.

35
00:02:22,259 --> 00:02:25,594
Pray, people. We want
God in the building today.

36
00:02:25,696 --> 00:02:28,496
- What time are we pitching you?
- Yeah, is there an order?

37
00:02:28,598 --> 00:02:31,394
You people are adults. You decide
the order. I decide whose department

38
00:02:31,418 --> 00:02:32,767
gets the million dollars.

39
00:02:32,869 --> 00:02:35,988
I love a good dogfight.

40
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:38,840
He can be intimidating.
Once you get in the room.

41
00:02:38,942 --> 00:02:40,776
- Really?
- Oh, yeah.

42
00:02:40,878 --> 00:02:43,206
When I pitched my cartilage
research last year, he was all ticked off

43
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:45,713
'cause I had a typo in
my table of contents.

44
00:02:45,815 --> 00:02:48,516
- You had a table of contents?
- Yeah.

45
00:02:53,156 --> 00:02:56,758
What? I love a
good dogfight, too.

46
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:58,460
Ruff!

47
00:02:58,562 --> 00:03:00,506
It's my case. You gonna
hand me over the chart?

48
00:03:00,530 --> 00:03:04,565
What factors would lead a patient
to want breast reduction surgery?

49
00:03:04,668 --> 00:03:07,802
Neck pain, back
pain, balance issues.

50
00:03:07,904 --> 00:03:09,704
- Hand it over.
- Keep trying.

51
00:03:09,806 --> 00:03:11,651
I don't know.
Maybe she's a prude.

52
00:03:11,675 --> 00:03:14,654
Doesn't want everyone staring at her
all the time. Maybe she's embarrassed.

53
00:03:14,678 --> 00:03:17,629
No. But you're getting warmer.

54
00:03:20,184 --> 00:03:22,868
- Hi, I'm Dr. Karev.
- Mindy Gruberman.

55
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:27,672
- Nice to meet you.
- I can work with that.

56
00:03:27,774 --> 00:03:28,857
She's not the patient.

57
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:31,154
Dr. Robbins. You'll be
on my service, too, huh?

58
00:03:31,178 --> 00:03:33,845
Dr. Karev's gonna be
our team leader today.

59
00:03:33,947 --> 00:03:36,798
Excuse me.

60
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,150
Honey, quit futzing with
the gown and come out here.

61
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:40,702
The doctors want to see you.

62
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,822
What's up?

63
00:03:50,414 --> 00:03:53,849
Ms. Radigan, you're still having these
headaches and ringing in the ears?

64
00:03:53,951 --> 00:03:56,484
All day long. It's
driving me crazy.

65
00:03:56,586 --> 00:03:58,854
It's caused by a build-up
of fluid in your skull.

66
00:03:58,956 --> 00:04:00,836
So, what we will
do is insert a shunt,

67
00:04:00,874 --> 00:04:02,836
and that will relieve the
pressure on your brain.

68
00:04:02,860 --> 00:04:06,678
What do you mean "we"? You're doing
the actual tube part in the brain, right?

69
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:09,326
- Not them?
- Excuse her. She's a school teacher,

70
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:12,451
she talks to everyone like they're
hiding gum behind their back.

71
00:04:12,553 --> 00:04:16,805
It's all right. She can ask questions.
Dr. Grey and Dr. Avery are residents,

72
00:04:16,907 --> 00:04:19,919
they're very talented. One of them
will be performing the procedure,

73
00:04:19,943 --> 00:04:22,160
- and I will be observing.
- A trainee?

74
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:25,147
Cutting into Ellie's brain? No.

75
00:04:25,249 --> 00:04:29,217
I know it sounds like a leap, but
these doctors study and assist for years.

76
00:04:29,319 --> 00:04:31,047
At some point, we
have to let them operate.

77
00:04:31,071 --> 00:04:34,000
- It's how we make new surgeons.
- Let them learn
on someone else.

78
00:04:34,024 --> 00:04:36,758
Who? Someone who's too
scared to interrogate the doctors?

79
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:40,245
They have to learn on someone,
might as well be an old lady.

80
00:04:40,347 --> 00:04:43,865
You're my old lady.
This should be my call.

81
00:04:43,984 --> 00:04:46,162
I won't let them move a muscle
without my direction and approval.

82
00:04:46,186 --> 00:04:49,938
You're a teacher,
Joanne. Let the kids learn.

83
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:55,543
She's my life. She has
been my life for 40 years.

84
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:57,645
Do you hear me?

85
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:00,865
I hear you.

86
00:05:00,951 --> 00:05:04,285
<i>Radiology, contact...</i>

87
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:07,033
- Who gets to cut?
- I want to get a look
at both of you

88
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:08,735
with a drill before I
decide who gets the shunt.

89
00:05:08,759 --> 00:05:10,636
Skills lab seems
like a fair way to go.

90
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:13,461
Competing with the wife.
Like that's not a stacked deck.

91
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:16,164
Well, it's a game, really.
So all you have to do is win.

92
00:05:16,266 --> 00:05:17,732
Which you won't.

93
00:05:17,834 --> 00:05:21,319
I don't like the idea of
teenagers getting plastic surgery.

94
00:05:21,421 --> 00:05:23,166
If the growths were on his
face, you wouldn't have a problem

95
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:25,351
- with him wanting them removed.
- Yeah, but I
might have a problem

96
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:29,577
- with Karev removing them.
- I'll give you that.

97
00:05:29,679 --> 00:05:34,098
- Oof! What happened?
- Karev's about
to do a gynecomastia

98
00:05:34,201 --> 00:05:36,818
- surgery on a 13-year-old.
- Oh, Karev's fine.

99
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,848
He's done way bigger
procedures than that.

100
00:05:38,872 --> 00:05:41,417
You two would just rather worry about
him than about your, uh, presentations

101
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:43,642
- to the chief.
- Oh! I'm not worried.

102
00:05:43,744 --> 00:05:47,162
The money's going to the tiny humans.
No one ever says no to the tiny humans.

103
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:49,363
Oh. OK.

104
00:05:51,468 --> 00:05:54,385
- What?
- Well...

105
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:57,299
You're not gonna cry, 'cause
you find the chief intimidating?

106
00:05:57,323 --> 00:05:59,640
- No!
- Good!

107
00:05:59,742 --> 00:06:03,327
- Good. OK.
- I have work to do.

108
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:05,079
Bye.

109
00:06:06,483 --> 00:06:08,177
What, are you trying
to psych her out?

110
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,801
Ortho needs the money.

111
00:06:09,903 --> 00:06:11,981
She and the friggin' tiny humans
have all the help they need already.

112
00:06:12,005 --> 00:06:16,825
- I'm getting the money. Let it go.
- Oh, OK.

113
00:06:16,927 --> 00:06:21,646
- Why wouldn't I?
- Well, because you never
prepare for anything,

114
00:06:21,749 --> 00:06:24,332
you think you'll get by on
your good looks and charm

115
00:06:24,434 --> 00:06:27,151
and the brilliance that
pops off the top of your head.

116
00:06:27,253 --> 00:06:29,905
Yeah, 'cause it always works.

117
00:06:30,007 --> 00:06:32,857
Mm... Uh-huh.

118
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,333
Roy Henley, 57, was
admitted two days ago

119
00:06:42,436 --> 00:06:44,870
with severe wheezing from
pulmonary hypertension.

120
00:06:44,971 --> 00:06:47,606
- Which basically means...
- I can't breathe for crap.

121
00:06:47,691 --> 00:06:51,292
We're gonna run some tests that
should help us decide how to proceed.

122
00:06:51,394 --> 00:06:54,474
You can run all the tests you
want. But what I need is new lungs.

123
00:06:54,498 --> 00:06:59,784
My doctor said I was gonna need
'em one day, but I was too healthy for it.

124
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:06,574
I bet I'm not too healthy now.

125
00:07:07,410 --> 00:07:09,244
Dr. Yang?

126
00:07:13,917 --> 00:07:15,667
We'll run some tests.

127
00:07:17,754 --> 00:07:22,073
Uh, Mr. Henley, you listed your
daughter as your emergency contact.

128
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:25,660
- Is she here with you today?
- No, she lives
over in Aberdeen.

129
00:07:25,762 --> 00:07:28,413
- I don't want to trouble her.
- Is there anyone here with you?

130
00:07:28,515 --> 00:07:31,082
I'm a tough old dog. I
don't need a chaperone.

131
00:07:31,184 --> 00:07:34,252
Sir, your condition is serious.

132
00:07:34,354 --> 00:07:37,772
It might be time to
trouble your daughter.

133
00:07:40,176 --> 00:07:43,111
- We think he's
a transplant candidate?
- Do we?

134
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:46,748
At this point, I don't think there's
anything else we can do. Right?

135
00:07:46,850 --> 00:07:49,017
Dr. Yang? Do you agree?

136
00:07:49,119 --> 00:07:51,853
I don't know.

137
00:07:51,955 --> 00:07:54,216
- You don't know if you agree?
- - He'd have to be approved

138
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,557
by the transplant team
before going on the waiting list.

139
00:07:56,659 --> 00:07:59,644
- Do we convene a panel?
- Yang, do we?

140
00:07:59,746 --> 00:08:01,496
I couldn't say.

141
00:08:01,598 --> 00:08:05,533
He's running out of time. I say
we convene the panel for today.

142
00:08:05,635 --> 00:08:07,446
OK, convene the
panel. And then what?

143
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:11,772
I get some interns to order
Mr. Henley's tests. On it.

144
00:08:11,874 --> 00:08:14,826
Dr. Yang. "I don't know"?

145
00:08:16,179 --> 00:08:19,046
I'm here, I am trying,
but taking point...

146
00:08:19,149 --> 00:08:23,300
I am not asking you to be in an
OR. I am asking you to say something.

147
00:08:23,403 --> 00:08:26,337
To participate. We're
at a crossroads, Yang.

148
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:29,491
A crossroads where you
either get in the game...

149
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:34,095
or I tell Richard it's
time to send you home.

150
00:08:45,825 --> 00:08:47,825
Imagine. Seattle Grace.

151
00:08:47,928 --> 00:08:50,195
The hospital that made
heart surgery obsolete.

152
00:08:50,297 --> 00:08:53,514
That's a big claim.

153
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:56,601
If the five million Americans
who suffer from heart failure

154
00:08:56,703 --> 00:08:59,271
could simply just regenerate
their own damaged hearts...

155
00:08:59,373 --> 00:09:03,574
It sounds like magic, but
it's possible. It's happening.

156
00:09:03,676 --> 00:09:06,677
Dr. Altman, stem cell
research is on the cutting edge

157
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:09,647
of every field of
medicine. Why cardio?

158
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:13,751
Well, Cardio and Neuro are
the beacons of this hospital.

159
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:16,254
They're what put you on the map.

160
00:09:16,339 --> 00:09:20,141
But you know what? You
can't give this money to Neuro.

161
00:09:20,243 --> 00:09:24,428
Neuro isn't even really a department.
It's just one strong surgeon.

162
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:27,015
You're better off putting your
money onto a deeper bench.

163
00:09:27,117 --> 00:09:31,152
- What do you mean?
- Well, Shepherd, he's
like a charismatic cult leader.

164
00:09:31,254 --> 00:09:35,423
He's very appealing and he's got a bunch
of people hiding in his shadows. But...

165
00:09:35,525 --> 00:09:37,825
Don't get me wrong,
he is a great surgeon.

166
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:42,297
And he can pull off a flashy
procedure. But is he cultivating talent?

167
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:45,766
Is he taking the time to teach your
residents, knowing when to push

168
00:09:45,869 --> 00:09:49,687
and dishing out tough love when
they need it? That's the hard part.

169
00:09:49,789 --> 00:09:52,423
I don't know, maybe Shepherd
just doesn't like competition.

170
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:57,962
He tried to fire me. Not that
I'm holding a grudge or anything.

171
00:09:59,198 --> 00:10:03,251
Well, not much of one, anyway.

172
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:06,538
I'm, uh...

173
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,290
I feel like I should
have stuck to my notes.

174
00:10:11,344 --> 00:10:13,656
- Is Teddy saying
you could be fired?
- Sounded that way.

175
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,497
Well, is she trying to
scare you? Is it working?

176
00:10:16,599 --> 00:10:19,500
- I don't think so.
- Oh! Damn it.

177
00:10:19,602 --> 00:10:21,903
- What's his problem?
- Derek's got us competing

178
00:10:22,005 --> 00:10:24,439
for a brain shunt insertion.
The egg is the skull.

179
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:27,575
You can break the shell, but
you can't break the membrane.

180
00:10:27,677 --> 00:10:29,272
- Damn it!
- I feel bad for him.

181
00:10:29,296 --> 00:10:32,880
He's kind of losing it.

182
00:10:32,982 --> 00:10:35,683
I shouldn't be in
charge of anybody.

183
00:10:35,785 --> 00:10:39,971
Just put one foot in front of the
other. Just get through the day.

184
00:10:40,073 --> 00:10:43,474
Grey! You broke
my concentration.

185
00:10:43,576 --> 00:10:47,345
Sorry. Um, hey. Post-ops look
good, so if there's nothing else...

186
00:10:47,447 --> 00:10:51,165
Oh, could you discharge 1224?
And his chart needs to be dictated.

187
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:54,919
Uh, yes. It's gonna have to wait
until after I check on Torres' knee girl,

188
00:10:55,021 --> 00:10:56,453
turf the window jumper to Psych,

189
00:10:56,556 --> 00:10:58,300
remove a june bug from
some kid's ear in the pit,

190
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:00,859
write meds for screaming kidney
stones guy and then deliver labs

191
00:11:00,961 --> 00:11:02,944
- to my goiter lady.
- Stop bragging.

192
00:11:03,046 --> 00:11:05,613
I can't. I was born
for this kind of day.

193
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:14,072
No. Stop.

194
00:11:14,174 --> 00:11:15,706
Seth. No.

195
00:11:15,808 --> 00:11:18,487
- OK? This can
wait a couple years.
- Mom!

196
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:21,563
You said this was my decision!
You said after my bar mitzvah,

197
00:11:21,665 --> 00:11:23,392
I'd be a man and I could decide.

198
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:25,661
That is because we thought by
13, you'd make the mature decision.

199
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:27,613
You can't cut off the
parts of your body

200
00:11:27,637 --> 00:11:31,689
that you don't like, all right? I don't
like my thighs or my saggy arms

201
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:34,658
or my chin, but if we all
cut off the parts we don't like,

202
00:11:34,761 --> 00:11:36,694
- we'd all have nothing left.
- Mom!

203
00:11:36,796 --> 00:11:40,431
Seth! Your father has the
exact same chest as you,

204
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:43,151
and nobody thinks he's a woman.

205
00:11:44,053 --> 00:11:46,804
Would you please talk to her?

206
00:11:46,907 --> 00:11:48,589
I'm calling your father.

207
00:11:51,361 --> 00:11:56,480
They call me Booby at
school. Man-boobs, Double D.

208
00:11:56,582 --> 00:11:58,983
Some kid keeps hanging
a bra on my locker.

209
00:11:59,085 --> 00:12:01,485
I'm starting high
school in a year.

210
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:05,190
It's gonna be all new
people. I just wanna start over.

211
00:12:05,292 --> 00:12:09,510
I wanna be normal
like everyone else.

212
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,341
Why can't we just
skip the panel?

213
00:12:12,365 --> 00:12:13,698
We know I need the lungs.

214
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,411
Not everyone makes a
good transplant candidate.

215
00:12:15,435 --> 00:12:17,613
If someone can't reliably
take their anti-rejection meds...

216
00:12:17,637 --> 00:12:19,937
- I can.
- Or has severe disease

217
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:21,923
- in another organ...
- I don't.

218
00:12:22,025 --> 00:12:23,975
There are just
a lot of indicators

219
00:12:24,077 --> 00:12:25,638
as to whether a
person is strong enough

220
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:28,996
- to survive the surgery.
- I wanna know what she thinks.

221
00:12:29,098 --> 00:12:32,767
The one with the
sourpuss on her face.

222
00:12:34,604 --> 00:12:36,838
I don't have a sourpuss.
This is just my face.

223
00:12:36,940 --> 00:12:39,323
It's true. It is just her face.

224
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,726
You think I'll pass the panel?

225
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:47,765
I couldn't say.

226
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:50,435
Cheer up, sourpuss.

227
00:12:50,536 --> 00:12:53,488
You're young,
you got your health.

